subject: Athletics and Sports
lead_paragraph: The former major league pitcher Rick Rhoden double-bogeyed the final hole to drop into a three-way tie for the lead after the third round of the Champions Tour’s national qualifying tournament. Rhoden shot a par 72 to match Jack Ferenz (69) and Scott Masingill (70) at six-under 210 on the TPC Eagle Trace in Coral Springs, Fla. After the fourth round today, the low 30 players and ties will earn spots into open qualifiers at all co-sponsored events on the 2008 Champions Tour.
